willie velasquez whose 16year effort 
to increase hispanic voter registration led to the ethnic group 
becoming a viable political force died wednesday of cancer he was 
44 
in 1972 velasquez helped found the svrep a nonprofit 
organization that initially sought to register hispanic voters and 
later with other organizations sued local governments to convert 
from atlarge voting systems to singlemember districts to assure 
equal hispanic representation 
he gained politicians respect for his unpartisan effort to 
increase hispanic voter registration which has increased from 25 
million in 1976 to an expected 5 million for the general election 
in november 
