press newsman who retired in 1968 after 38 years with the news 
service died thursday at age 83 
hoyman worked at the des moines iowa tribune capital before 
joining the ap in pierre he transferred to the seattle bureau in 
1937 hoyman was named news editor in seattle in 1939 a post he 
held until his retirement 
after his retirement he was manager of the news election service 
for washington state for several years 
