<TEXT>
portauprince haiti ap president leslie manigat has 
rejected the transfers of several highranking army officers 
publicly challenging for the first time the powerful military 
command that ensured his election 
the apparent power struggle began when lt gen henri namphy 
head of the threeman junta that ran haiti until manigats election 
in january ordered the transfers or retirements 
manigat on wednesday overruled the orders claiming they were 
unconstitutional since he had not been consulted 
on wednesday night the army general staff issued a statement 
pledging loyalty to manigat and delaying the transfer orders 
it has been decided after a meeting with the president and 
the minister of defense to temporarily put off the above mentioned 
steps said the statement broadcast on the private radio haiti 
inter 
the transfer and retirement of certain highranking officers 
and other officers decided tuesday morning by the 
commanderinchief had been rescinded to avoid a major 
crisis said the statement from the national palace read on local 
radio stations 
it was unclear whether manigat had prevailed 
the situation is grave said a western diplomat speaking on 
condition of anonymity either the general submits to manigats 
ultimatum or there will be a standoff between the government and 
the army there is fear of a clash 
one of the officers namphy tried to reassign is col jeanclaude 
paul who heads the widelyfeared dessalines battalion and was 
indicted in the united states on drug trafficking charges in march 
haiti inter quoting an unidentified military source said 
namphy ordered paul relieved of his command of the 700man 
battalion and named assistant chief of staff a largely 
administrative position 
soldiers under pauls command have been blamed for widespread 
violence against voters that forced the cancellation of last 
novembers independently adminstrated general elections and left 
more than 30 people dead 
manigat the armys candidate in the jan 17 juntarun 
elections has always claimed that he could govern independent of 
the army which has controlled haiti during most of its 184year 
history 
a government spokeswoman said wednesday that everyone was 
waiting to see what would happen 
this is certainly a moment of crisis said anaise chavenet 
spokeswoman for the ministry of information 
manigat scheduled a news conference for this morning 
the armys statement signed by general secretary of the general 
staff col gary leon also said the high command reaffirmed its 
unreserved loyalty to the government of the state within the 
framework of constitutional and legal provisions 
namphy was head of the threeman junta that ruled haiti for two 
years after dictator jeanclaude duvalier fled into exile in france 
in february 1986 
manigat a former political science professor was elected in 
armysupervised balloting that was boycotted by the opposition that 
foreign observers said was fraught with fraud 
the united states cut off most of its aid to haiti after the 
aborted november balloting 
paul was indicted in march by a grand jury in miami on charges 
of conspiring to import 220 pounds of cocaine into the united 
states from latin america in december 1986 he has denied the 
charges 
last week foreign minister gerard latortue said in washington 
dc that his government is ready to open an investigation into 
pauls alleged drug connection as soon as it officially receives 
the evidence from the united states 
us embassy spokesman jeffrey lite said details of the charges 
were delivered to haitian authorities last week 
manigat a social democrat considered rightofcenter and 
staunchly anticommunist has done little to alleviate haitis most 
pressing problems 
haiti which a population of 6 million is the poorest country 
in the western hemisphere it shares the island of hispaniola with 
the dominican republic 
</TEXT>
