<TEXT>
long island lighting cos board of 
directors unanimously approved an agreement with the state under 
which the completed but unused shoreham nuclear power plant would 
be torn down 
it would be the first time in the nation that a completed 
nuclear plant was abandoned 
under the proposal approved wednesday the utility would 
continue as a privately owned company and be provided with annual 
rate hikes of about 5 percent over 10 years 
the agreement is subject to the approval of various state 
agencies and the legislature it calls for the utility to sell the 
53 billion plant to the state for 1 the plant would then be 
torn down 
the plant 50 miles from manhattan on long island was completed 
in 1984 the utility failed to obtain an operating license because 
the state and local governments refused to participate in emergency 
planning arguing it was impossible to evacuate the surrounding 
area in an accident 
