a pygmy killer whale beached itself 
and died at the isle of palms of wounds it apparently suffered from 
sharks authorities say 
the 7footlong whale a type rarely seen was spotted 
wednesday it beached itself twice but was helped back into the 
water by swimmers then pulled back ashore because police feared it 
would attract sharks to the crowded beach said police cpl les 
griffin 
the whale died before a veterinarian arrived officials said 
the dead whale was examined by al sanders curator of natural 
science at the charleston museum and andrew mount a research 
analyst with the south carolina sea grant consortium 
it was the only second stranding of a pygmy killer whale on 
record in the state with the first two years ago sanders said 
the wounds on the whales back were probably caused by sharks 
he said 
