a coalition of consumer groups on thursday 
gave a producer of frozen yogurt the manufacturer of audi 
automobiles and eight other advertisers backhanded awards for 
presenting the most misleading commercials 
the fourth annual harlan page hubbard memorial awards named for 
a 19th century advertising pioneer who promoted patent medicines as 
cures for virtually all ills were announced at a ceremony that 
drew none of the winners 
one prize went to dannon frozen yogurt on a stick for an ad 
showing a 6yearold girl in a swimming suit critics charged that 
the image imposed a sexual message on little girls 
we never imagined that consumers would take that message 
