nonviolent action to march down university avenue to the 
metropolitan toronto convention center where the leaders will meet 
demonstrators could occupy the attention of police and allow 
terrorists to act nadeau said 
he said police also worry about random attacks by unstable 
persons like john hinckley jr who shot and wounded reagan in 
1981 
despite its setting in a city of 34 million people the summit 
will take place in a security cocoon at no time will the 
delegates be on public view said toronto police chief jack marks 
local resident alex mackenzie called it ironic that reagan 
walked the streets of moscow a place he once dubbed an evil 
empire but toronto is not considered safe enough for him to 
emerge from his armored limousine 
