it 
the porcelana billboards show the product name a closeup 
photograph of two lightskinned black women and the words faded 
beauties of philadelphia one billboard before it was covered by 
a new advertisement was embellished with graffiti that changed 
faded beauties to read faded pride and the words stop 
racist advertising were written across it 
fade creams are frequently advertised in blackoriented 
magazines for correcting uneven skin tones or diminishing scars and 
blemishes but critics say the billboards imply lighter is better 
officials for the los angelesbased dep corp which makes and 
distributes porcelana declined to comment on thursday 
porcelana might not have meant to promote the cream as an 
overall skin lightener but the possibility is the crux of the 
problem said paul bennett executive editor of the philadelphia 
tribune a triweekly that is one of the oldest blackowned papers 
in the united states 
i dont know if its out and out blatant racism that makes for 
these kind of decisions but there seems to be a certain lack of 
sensitivity that is born of out of some form of racist attitude 
bennett said 
the issue is not so much that particular billboard bennett 
said the issue is the treatment of black folks in advertising 
across the board 
a penn state researcher who has studied the effects of 
minoritytargeted advertising said 
the controversy might be an example of a company misjudging the 
message it sends to consumers said jerome williams a marketing 
professor at penn state who has studied the effects of 
minoritytargeted advertising 
even if they didnt mean to offend what you have to be 
concerned with is the decoded message what did it mean to the 
consumer williams said 
if that decoded message is leading to a negative perception 
regardless of the intent of the advertiser they should change the 
advertisement 
in an atmosphere of increased minority pride and activism 
advertisers can find themselves in trouble if they fail to consider 
the sensitivity of their target group he said 
black consumers wield well more than 200 billion of purchasing 
power while hispanic consumers have more than 100 billion 
williams said 
i think youre going to find more and more consumers who are 
going to use that purchasing power to reward those advertisers who 
are sensitive to their issues williams said 
advertisers who aggravate minority consumers may find that 
consumers not only avoid a product but may actively campaign 
against it williams said 
