the meeting 
at last years sevennation economic summit president reagan 
unveiled a proposal for phasing out government subsidies to farmers 
by the end of the century the eec has rejected the idea saying it 
supports coordinated cuts in subsidies but that some government aid 
will always be necessary to properly manage farm markets 
last fall the eec proposed what it called short term 
measures aimed at easing immediate problems of overproduction of 
sugar grain and other crops the united states has criticized this 
approach 
farm reform is a central theme of the current uruguay round of 
international trade liberalization negotiations being held under 
the auspices of the 93nation general agreement on tariffs and 
trade 
delors also said discussions of key economic and trade issues at 
toronto would be made more difficult by the fact that reagan will 
soon leave office and the us presidential election contest is 
heating up 
this will make discussion of the outlook for the world economy 
in 1989 and 1990 a little bit more difficult delors said adding 
that it also would hamper discussion of the gatt trade 
liberalization talks 
