more than 16 per 1000 in face value in late afternoon 
further pressuring the markets was a government report that 
showed operating rates at american factories mines and utilities 
rose to 829 percent in may the highest level in more than eight 
years 
the report well above market expectations was interpreted as a 
sign that inflation may be lurking on the horizon 
analysts fear a crack in investors confidence which has been 
building gradually but lower stock prices also could bring out 
some bargain hunters 
